about shippeinge, for y. future shall send my remeses to you donly
dervicbley, & shall please mee best, because I must cesres iend,
with m. Bollengere oneley for 3ou. y french are so strons att zea
come out of Duynquerque, that they shall take all shins that
come, they have taken a whele fleet from Joland for ostend
though there was 5 dutelimer of wair & 3 snall ones of osterd
for convoy y convoyes att hull for Amst is to little to rapose
these rwatiers because they some them selves mescreadres
so Jeare not much of all my ordre bee not fulley com
pleated by y Amst. convoy. & if y. kersies bee not cheap
& good to 3o coutent, buy non principalley if you scrose
bliey will bee cheaper in mas or Puno next, & if bought
